lyIfValueIsSet can be define by user, null|\\\"null\\\"|\\\"empty\\\" or value a user defines. Be carefull, there is difference between null and \\\"null\\\", to be \\\"null\\\" is must be defined by user.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetVariables\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Tuple`2[System.Object,System.Object]]\",\"Name\":\"keyValues\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"keyIsDynamic\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"onlyIfValueIsNot\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set value on variables. If value is json, make sure to format it as valid json, use double quote(\\\") by escaping it.  onlyIfValueIsSet can be define by user, null|\\\"null\\\"|\\\"empty\\\" or value a user defines. Be carefull, there is difference between null and \\\"null\\\", to be \\\"null\\\" is must be defined by user.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetValuesOnVariables\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"keyValues\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"keyIsDynamic\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"onlyIfValueIsNot\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set default value on variables if not set, good for setting value if variable is empty. Number can be represented with _, e.g. 100_000. If value is json, make sure to format it as valid json, use double quote(\\\") by escaping it.  onlyIfValueIsSet can be define by user, null|\\\"null\\\"|\\\"empty\\\" or value a user defines. Be carefull, there is difference between null and \\\"null\\\", to be \\\"null\\\" is must be defined by user.\\nEx